We do have a question right now from John.

00:37:27.140 --> 00:37:38.500
John says, "Coming from a country
 that lacks enforcing digital accessibility,

00:37:39.020 --> 00:37:45.980
how can an individual or my company
 help to push this initiative forward?"

00:37:47.380 --> 00:37:56.860
Femi: I think the first thing
 is to learn more about accessibility standards.

00:37:57.060 --> 00:38:02.380
There is the WCAG 2.1,
which is a global standard.

00:38:02.500 --> 00:38:04.940
I think that's the first step,

00:38:05.140 --> 00:38:08.420
learning and also introducing
that in the company.

00:38:08.580 --> 00:38:10.620
To push the initiative forward,

00:38:10.860 --> 00:38:13.340
as I mentioned,
 I think one of the best ways

00:38:13.460 --> 00:38:14.980
is reaching out to advocacy groups.

00:38:15.140 --> 00:38:18.580
I'm not sure
what country you're from,

00:38:18.700 --> 00:38:21.060
but reaching out
to advocacy groups and working

00:38:21.180 --> 00:38:26.940
with advocacy groups and also
spreading awareness, just like I'm doing now.

00:38:27.100 --> 00:38:29.340
I think spreading awareness
 is very important.

00:38:29.460 --> 00:38:32.660
Spreading awareness
 is the first thing to do

00:38:32.820 --> 00:38:36.220
to actually push this forward
 and also reaching out

00:38:36.340 --> 00:38:38.300
to advocacy groups to work with them.

00:38:40.620 --> 00:38:42.660
Yigakpoa: Thank you so much, Femi.

00:38:42.820 --> 00:38:45.660
We have another amazing
question from Manto.

00:38:45.780 --> 00:38:48.940
And Manto says, "As someone
 who has started an initiative

00:38:49.100 --> 00:38:51.820
to empower persons
with disabilities in Africa,

00:38:51.980 --> 00:38:56.580
specifically Cameroon,
what advice can you give to me

00:38:56.780 --> 00:39:00.500
on how to support or how
to get support from the continent?"

00:39:02.500 --> 00:39:03.260
Femi: Great.

00:39:03.420 --> 00:39:07.740
I have also thought about this
 as I'm working on my research.

00:39:07.900 --> 00:39:11.260
How do I get support from the country?

00:39:11.420 --> 00:39:16.220
As I mentioned, I have,
I reached out to some advocacy groups.

00:39:16.340 --> 00:39:21.980
There is the WCAPD,
 it's the Western Cape Association for People

00:39:22.100 --> 00:39:26.020
with Disabilities,
and they have been very supportive

00:39:26.180 --> 00:39:32.540
because they are NGOs
that are more connected to the government.

00:39:32.660 --> 00:39:36.940
They have been very supportive
 and they have really tried

00:39:37.020 --> 00:39:41.220
to give me as more information
 that I need for my research

00:39:41.300 --> 00:39:49.820
and they are willing to help
in pushing this case forward in the country.

00:39:49.980 --> 00:39:54.060
I would say one of the ways to get support
 is also reaching out to advocacy groups.

00:39:55.860 --> 00:39:57.980
You say you're from Cameroon.

